<zk>
1. When you resize panel's width, all of the width in the same column will be updated.
<separator/>
2. After resize the panel's width and height, you can move it to another place by drag and drop, the size of that panel should keep the same as before dragged.
<portallayout>
    <portalchildren width="30%">
        <panel id="p1" height="150px" title="Panel 1" sizable="true" border="normal">
            <panelchildren>
                <div width="100%" height="100%" style="background-color: blue"/>
            </panelchildren>
        </panel>
        <panel id="p2" height="300px" title="Panel 2" sizable="true" border="normal">
            <panelchildren>
                <div width="100%" height="100%" style="background-color: green"/>
            </panelchildren>
        </panel>
    </portalchildren>
    <portalchildren width="70%">
        <panel id="p3" height="150px" title="Panel 3" sizable="true">
            <panelchildren>
                <div width="100%" height="100%" style="background-color: red"/>
            </panelchildren>
        </panel>
    </portalchildren>
</portallayout>
</zk>